As a Christian, I can say that I believe prostitution is wrong. And I do not think any parent of any little girl-regardless of their beliefs-will say that they want this for their daughter. But prostitution has always been here, and there is no way to stop it. I humbly believe that if these young women had legal protection, their live would be safer. I do not believe this would result in more women-or young men-practicing prostitution, but I do believe that venereal disease could be controlled and the horrible abuses that pimps do on prositutes could be stopped because the women have recourse to legal protection. There is no one that will seriously argue that prostitution will stop. And no good man will patronize prostitutes. But isn't it right to provide some protection of the law for them? Are they less human, less likely to be abused? I think more likely!! It is simply being humane.
